<div class="expanded">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif">Our Business:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Europe Card Services (ECS) is the number one credit card lender in Europe, with operations in the United Kingdom, Ireland and Spain serving over seven million customers. We have been issuing credit cards in Europe since 1993 through our subsidiary, MBNA Europe Bank Limited, which forms part of our Global Consumer and Small Business Banking Group.</p>
<p class="bac">Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America is the recognised leader in affinity marketing with approximately 4,000 affinity partners worldwide. We are also the leading issuer of co-branded credit cards in Europe with over 800 partners such as Virgin Money, BMI, BT, Sony, WWF, Breakthrough Breast Cancer, The National Trust and most premier football and rugby clubs. These affinity relationships allow our customers to earn great rewards and discounts or contribute to worthwhile causes through their everyday credit card purchases.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Overview:</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Our graduate intake will be based around a number of specialist streams.</li>
	<li>Graduate programme aims to develop and support future leaders of the business.</li>
	<li>All streams will involve you as an active team member in the department(s) to which your discipline relates.</li>
	<li>You will gain broad exposure to the entire ECS business.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Qualifications:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">You must be able to combine academic aptitude, strategic and creative thinking, and written and oral communications skills. In addition, you must have obtained or are realistically expecting to obtain a minimum 2:2 degree or equivalent in a discipline directly relating to the scheme for which you are applying. Underlying all this, you must demonstrate dedication to a career in an environment that is highly commercial and focused on excellent customer service.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Training:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">You will develop technical, personal and professional skills, as well as learning more about Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America&#39;s capabilities and culture. This will be gained by working within the business areas that relate to your discipline, as well as through classroom training and other development opportunities, enabling effective integration into the business and the broader Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Corporation.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Locations:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">All Europe Card Services graduate streams will be based in Chester (UK).</p>
</div></div>

